ack_count += 1\n            else:  # ball == '0'\n                steps += black_count\n        \n        return steps\n\n# Example usage:\n# sol = Solution()\n# print(sol.minimumSteps(\"101\"))  # Output: 1\n# print(sol.minimumSteps(\"100\"))  # Output: 2\n# print(sol.minimumSteps(\"0111\")) # Output: 0\n```\n\nThis solution works in O(n) time complexity, where n is the length of the string `s`. This is efficient given the constraints. The space complexity is O(1) since we are only using a few extra variables.", "estimated_date": 1700352000000}